==Finnish==
{{Finnish index|ka}}
===Etymology===
A compound of kah- and deksan. The former comes from [[kaksi]], while the latter is from an Iranian language, compare Kurdish [[deh]]. So the compound originally meant two (from) ten.
===Cardinal Number===
'''kahdeksan'''

#[[eight]]

